      "widgets_values": [
        "# Pixal3D-ComfyUI Workflow\n\n  **Repo:** [Saganaki22/Pixal3D-ComfyUI](https://github.com/Saganaki22/Pixal3D-ComfyUI)\n\n  ## Models\n\n  - **Pixal3D:** [TencentARC/Pixal3D](https://huggingface.co/TencentARC/Pixal3D) →\n  `ComfyUI/models/Pixal3D/TencentARC_Pixal3D/`\n  - **MoGe:** [Comfy-Org/MoGe](https://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/MoGe) →\n  `ComfyUI/models/geometry_estimation/moge_1_vitl_fp16.safetensors` + `moge_2_vitl_normal_fp16.safetensors`\n  - **RMBG-2.0:** [briaai/RMBG-2.0](https://huggingface.co/briaai/RMBG-2.0) (gated) →\n  `ComfyUI/models/Pixal3D/briaai_RMBG-2.0/` <br> (Request access first)\n\n  ## Hardware\n\n  - VRAM: **20–32 GB** (1536_cascade ~32 GB, 1024_cascade may fit ~20 GB with native_low_vram)\n  - System RAM: **40 GB minimum**\n\n  ## Troubleshooting\n\n  If something goes wrong, **run Pixal3D Environment Check first** and paste the log along with the full error message\n  when opening an issue.\n\n  **Issues:** [Saganaki22/Pixal3D-ComfyUI/issues](https://github.com/Saganaki22/Pixal3D-ComfyUI/issues)\n\n  ### How to report an issue\n\n  1. Run **Pixal3D Environment Check** and copy the full output\n  2. Reproduce the error and copy the traceback/error message from the ComfyUI terminal\n  3. Include your hardware: GPU model, VRAM, system RAM\n  4. Include your stack: Python version, PyTorch version, CUDA version\n  5. Open a new issue at [Saganaki22/Pixal3D-ComfyUI/issues](https://github.com/Saganaki22/Pixal3D-ComfyUI/issues) with:\n     - A clear title describing the problem\n     - The Environment Check log\n     - The full error message / traceback\n     - Any steps you already tried"
      ],
